2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Stephens was born in 1420, in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir John Forrester Stephens, was 11 and his mother, Margaret de Didbrok, was 39. He married Alice Shaw in 1438, in Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1490, in his hometown, at the age of 70, and was buried in Gloucestershire, England."},"et":{"1420–1490":"1420–1490","1421–1462":"1421–1462","1424–1459":"1424–1459","1459–1505":"1459–1505","1409–Male":"1409–Surnud","1381–1428":"1381–1428","9 January 1428":"9. jaanuar 1428","1462":"1462","1381":"1381","1490":"1490","1459":"1459","1424":"1424","1434":"1434","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","1420":"1420","21 October 1459":"21. oktoober 1459","1409":"1409","1428":"1428","1505":"1505","1438":"1438","Lewynsmede, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lewynesmede, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"1420–1490":"1420–1490","1421–1462":"1421–1462","1424–1459":"1424–1459","1459–1505":"1459–1505","1409–Male":"1409–Kuollut","1381–1428":"1381–1428","9 January 1428":"9. tammikuuta 1428","1462":"1462","1381":"1381","1490":"1490","1459":"1459","1424":"1424","1434":"1434","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","1420":"1420","21 October 1459":"21. lokakuuta 1459","1409":"1409","1428":